    "PlaceNameModern":"Bahrain",
    "NameOfTraveler":"Lewes Vertomannus",
    "YearOfTravel":1503,
    "Description":"AFter that the tempestes were appeased, wee gave wynde to our sayles, and in shorte tyme arryued at an Ilande named Barbara, the Prince whereof, is a Mahumetan. The Ilande is not great, but fruitfull and well peopled : it hath abundance of flesh... Al theyr ryches, is in heardes of cattayle.",
