    "PlaceName":"Los Esclavos",
    "PlaceNameModern":"Los Esclavos, Guatemala",
    "NameOfTraveler":"Thomas Gage",
    "YearOfTravel":1637,
    "Description":"This Towne of los Esclavos standeth in a bottome by a river, over the which the Spaniards have built a very strong stone Bridge to goe in and out of the Town, for otherwise with mules there is no passing by reason of the violent and rapid streame of the water, and many rocks in the River, from which the water falleth down with great force.",
