    "PlaceNameModern":"Majorca",
    "NameOfTraveler":"Ruy Gonzalez de Clavijo",
    "YearOfTravel":1403,
    "Description":"On Saturday, the 28th of June, the vessel was off the island of Majorca, and so near that it could be seen very clearly ; and on Sunday she was off an island called Cabrera, on which there was a small castle ; and on Monday and Tuesday she made little way, owing to light winds ; but on Wednesday she was off the island of Micorca, and entered the gulf of Lyons. From Thursday to Saturday she passed across the gulf of Lyons with a fair wind ; ad on Sunday, which was S. John's day, she was off an Island called Linera, which is subject to the authrity of the viceroy of Aragon.",
