    "NameOfTraveler":"Ruy Gonzalez de Clavijo",
    "YearOfTravel":1403,
    "Description":"A little further on she passed other mountains, also on the main land, and came in sight of a town which is called Taracena, in the Roman territory, and twelve leagues distant from Rome. Between the sea and the town there were fruit gardens and tall trees, and between these gardens and the town there was a monastery, which was once occupied by nuns, but they had all been carried off by the Moors of Barbary.",
