    "YearOfTravel":1403,
    "Description":"On the same day, she passed Cape Minerva on the main land, and two high hills, between which there is a city called Amalfi, where they say the head of St. Andrew is preserved. At the hour of vespers, they beheld two masses of smoke fall from the heavens and reach the sea, and the water rose with violence, and with a great noise, and obscured the heavens, covering them with clouds: so they luffed the vessel as much as they were able, because they said that if those masses reached the carrack, they would surely sink her.",
