    "NameOfTraveler":"Ruy Gonzalez de Clavijo",
    "YearOfTravel":1403,
    "Description":"They also saw another island on the right hand, called Lipari, which is inhabited, and subject to king Lanzalago. In this island the veil of the blessed Saint Agueda is kept: and the island used to burn, but, owing to the prayers of the blessed Saint Agueda, it ceased to burn, together with other neighbouring islands; and when the other islands burn they take out this veil, and presently the fire ceases.",
