    "Description":"On the same afternoon they were off a place, belonging to the emperor, called Redea ; and in sight of an island called Calonimo, off the land of Turkey. On Monday morning they were near the same place, as there was little wind, so they anchored about two miles from the shore, and fifteen miles from Constantinople.",
