    "YearOfTravel":1403,
    "Description":"The city of Constantinople is surrounded by a high and strong wall, with towers. The wall has three angles, and from angle to angle there is a distance of six miles, so that the whole city is eighteen miles in circumference, which is six leagues; two sides facing the sea, and one facing the land.\n\nAt the angle which does not face the sea, on a hill, are the palaces of the emperor.",
