    "PlaceNameModern":"Sinop",
    "NameOfTraveler":"Ruy Gonzalez de Clavijo",
    "YearOfTravel":1404,
    "Description":"On Monday, the 31st of March, they sailed, and at vespers they arrived in the port of a city, which is called Sinope, and anchored there. This city belongs to Espandiar, and when the ambassadors arrived there, they found that he was not there, but in another city, three days journey distant, called Castamea,' with forty thousand men, fighting against the son of the Turk, who hated him, because he paid tribute to Timour Beg.",
