    "NameOfTraveler":"Ruy Gonzalez de Clavijo",
    "YearOfTravel":1404,
    "Description":"On Tuesday, in the afternoon, they departed, and, at a distance of two leagues, they came in sight of a great city, all in ruins,' on the right hand side of the road ; but there appeared towers and mosques, and the name of the place was Xahariprey. This was once the largest city in all that land, though it is now uninhabited.",
