    "NameOfTraveler":"Ruy Gonzalez de Clavijo",
    "YearOfTravel":1404,
    "Description":"There is also another great chapel, which Timour Beg has ordered to be built, for his own body, and it was not finished. They say that when he was here, a month ago, he did not like this chapel, saying that the door was low, and ordering it to be raised, and they are now working at it.",
    "Citation":"Clavijo, Ruy Gonzalez de. Narrative of the Embassy of Ruy Gonzalez De Clavijo to the Court of Timour, at Samarcand, A.d. 1403-6. Translated by CLements R. Markham. London: Printed for the Hakluyt Society, 1847. https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/000059571.",
