    "Description":"The mosque which the lord caused to be built, in honour of the mother of his wife Caño, was the most respected in the city. When it was finished, he thought the entrance was too low, so he ordered the building to be pulled down; and that it might be sooner rebuilt, he took charge of one part himself, and ordered his Meerzas to watch over the other.\n\n[Probably this building.]",
    "Citation":"Clavijo, Ruy Gonzalez de. Narrative of the Embassy of Ruy Gonzalez De Clavijo to the Court of Timour, at Samarcand, A.d. 1403-6. Translated by CLements R. Markham. London: Printed for the Hakluyt Society, 1847. https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/000059571.",
